  "golden": {
    "answer": "Circle launched CCTP V2 on Stellar on 2026-02-24 as domain 27. It burns native USDC on the source and mints native USDC on the destination. For Stellar G-, M-, or C-address recipients, use Circle's CctpForwarder path; a wrong mintRecipient or destinationCaller can strand funds. Stellar USDC uses 7 decimals while CCTP messages use 6, so the seventh outbound decimal remains on Stellar. On 2026-07-11, Circle's fee endpoint returned Fast/Standard 0/0 for domain 27→0 and 1 bp/0 for 0→27; re-query /v2/burn/USDC/fees. Circle transfer fees are separate from network resources, relayer, integrator, and any swap charges.",
    "keyFacts": [
      "CCTP V2 launched on Stellar on 2026-02-24 as domain 27 and uses burn, attestation, and mint for native USDC.",
      "Use Circle's CctpForwarder for Stellar G-, M-, or C-address recipients; incorrect mintRecipient or destinationCaller values can strand funds.",
      "Stellar USDC has 7 decimals while CCTP messages use 6; the seventh outbound decimal remains on Stellar.",
      "The 2026-07-11 fee probe found Fast/Standard 0/0 for 27→0 and 1 bp/0 for 0→27; callers must re-query /v2/burn/USDC/fees.",
      "Circle transfer fees are separate from network resource, relayer, integrator, and swap charges."
    ],
    "avoid": [
      "CCTP locks USDC and issues a wrapped Stellar token.",
      "Every CCTP route is permanently fee-free and exactly 1:1 after all costs."
    ],
    "notes": "Status-sensitive details are stated as of 2026-07-11; grade later sourced changes leniently and require dated primary evidence."
  },
